body.description: Dual channel 32GB DDR4 memory upgrade, consisting of 2 x 16GB modules. The Aegis G.Skill DDR4 Series is designed for entry-level computer gamers looking for excellent performance at a great price. 288 pins, 3000MHz memory module, PC4-24000 standard and CL16 timings (16-18-18-38). Operating at 1.35V, this memory generates less heat than standard DDR4 modules.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The Ideal Solution for Gaming PCs Named after the powerful shield of Greek gods, Aegis symbolizes strength and power. This new addition of DDR4 memory to the AEGIS family of gaming memory is designed for upgraded performance and high stability on the latest PC gaming systems. Give the quality performance boost your gaming rig deserves, no matter the game. Whether it’s FPS, RTS, MOBA, or MMORPG, let AEGIS Gaming DDR4 Memory be the strength of your gaming arsenal!

Designed for Gamers Available from a standard starting speed of DDR4-2133MHz, give the performance of your system a boost by increasing the amount of transfers per second over the previous generation of DDR3 memory. Upgrade your PC memory speed or capacity with the G.SKILL Aegis DDR4 series for a smoother gaming experience!

Built for Quality Built with the highest quality of hand-selected ICs and rigorously tested on major performance motherboard brands, the AEGIS Gaming DDR4 Memory is designed for the best compatibility and stability the widest selection of motherboards*. [*Please make sure to check the G.SKILL product webpage for the latest Qualified Vendors List (QVL).]

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great price for quality RAM
reviews.reviewText: Price was good for these, and they worked great, and speed was really good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Runs well, but detects at slower speed so you may need to manually set in bios
reviews.reviewText: This memory runs well, no issues. I was surprised to see that it was running at a much slower clock speed, but changed that in the bios and it is solid as a rock. Great value. Would purchase again. I have an AM4 setup and it is supposed to run better with two sticks than four, with the same amount of memory. So, I went with this two stick setup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Ram works great
reviews.reviewText: My computer needed DDR4-3000 speed ram in order to function at the highest efficiency, and this product delivered. Adding the ram to my computer made the device run faster. The ram is compatible with my AsRock motherboard and it has a G skill sticker over the memory modules. The ram looks just like the advertised picture. My computer immediately recognized the additional ram once installed. Many of the high-end games I play run better as well as the graphic design programs. This product is perfect for making running adobe software more efficiently on PC and thus cutting down my production time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Working well but speed not necessarily automatic
reviews.reviewText: On at least AMD based motherboards the speed is initially set to the best JEDEC profile. (I don't know on Intel based motherboards) The rated speed for these modules are stored in the XMP profile which AMD based board s don't automatically use. I DON'T KNOW IF THE BEST JEDEC TIMINGS ARE INCORRECT BECAUSE I HAD AN ISSUE WITH RANDOM SHUTDOWNS THAT DISAPPEARED AFTER BOTH CHECKING IF PSU FAN STOPPED AND SETTING MEMORY TO XMP SETTINGS. (Was my issue with memory or the PSU or even the motherboard? I guess I will never know)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 21, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for the money
reviews.reviewText: I have been using G.Skill memory for some time now. I have not had any issues with any of the sticks that I have purchased. The memory sticks are now running in all three of my PC's. They run fine when I adjust the timings to run my higher end bench tests. I can't speak to gaming simply because it's something that I don't run on any of my machines.

reviews.reviewTitle: Ottime ram per MSI Trident X visto il low profile
reviews.reviewText: Comprate per utilizzo cun un MSI Trident X che richiede delle ram che non vadano a toccare il dissipatore per la cpu, molto basso sulla scheda madre.Il mio sistema ha un intel di decima generazione che supporta al massimo 3000mhz di frequenza per le ram quindi erano perfette.Nessun problema nel montaggio.

Les barrettes de mémoires sont de très bonnes qualités; elles sont garanties à vie. Après, il faut savoir les paramétrer correctement dans le BIOS à 2133Mhz ou 2300Mhz pour qu'elles fonctionnent correctement. Apuuyez sur ALT+F10 OU F11 au bon moment du démarrage de l'ordinateur, puis choisissez le paramétrage "barrette de mémoires" pour finir sur la "fréquence MHz" du paramétrage). Faites attention, si la fréquence sélectionnée n'est pas la bonne, l'ordinateur s'éteindra automatiquement par mesure de sécurité anti cour-cicuit électrique.Par contre les services de transport DHL ne sont que des gros fainéants. Ils laissent un récépissé d'absence pour éviter d'aller chez les gens même si vous êtes présents, alors qu'ils leur suffirait de frapper à la porte pour les donner. Donc, il faut courir après le produit dans les points de relais pour les récupérer. Une HONTE quand les livraisons à domicile sont facturées!
